# This is a PUBLIC repo. Everything below is either machine-local state, a
# secret, or an audit artifact that can carry a crew token (`#g=...` — the
# capability credential that IS access to a crew's data). Deny by default.

# Secrets
.env*

# Node / Vercel
node_modules/
.vercel
.vercel/

# Claude Code: local state is ignored, but settings.json SHIPS — it holds the
# shared hooks every session on this repo relies on. Naming the exception here
# beats the old blanket `.claude/` rule, which claimed to ignore a directory
# that in fact had seven tracked files in it.
.claude/*
!.claude/settings.json

# Project memory (symlinked out of the repo; never belongs in a public one)
.claude-memory

# Audit + review artifacts. Walkers drive a real browser, and the Playwright MCP
# sandbox can only write INSIDE the repo — so screenshots land here no matter
# where they are pointed. A 2026-07-12 run dumped 50 stray PNGs into the repo
# root; a careless `git add -A` is exactly how one of those reaches the public.
screenshots/
.playwright-mcp/
.remember/
390/
768/
1440/
offline/

# Deny every image by default; name the three that actually ship.
*.png
!favicon.png
!icon-192.png
!icon-512.png
